    <stitle>DIAMONDLIFE&#8482; (BOSCH PIN SLIDE) DISC BRAKES For Vehicles Built Before June 3, 2002 - DESCRIPTION
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>Hydraulic pin slide disc brakes are two-piston sliding caliper brakes and are used at both front and
                rear wheels
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0404001">(Figure 1</hotlnk>
                and
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0404002">Figure 2)</hotlnk>. The pin slide caliper disc brake is made up of four major
                components: caliper, anchor plate, rotor and disc brake pads.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Several changes have been incorporated within the anchor plate assembly and caliper mounting
                        bolts on vehicles manufactured after June 3, 2002. It is important to recognize that these
                        changes are not found on disc brakes on vehicles manufactured before June 3, 2002, unless a
                        complete rebuild of the anchor plate assembly was performed on the vehicle. The components that
                        have changed are the leading and trailing guide pins
                        <hotlnk document="s040402_X0404013.xml" xrefid="f0404067">(Figure 67)</hotlnk>
                        <xref refid="f0404067"/>
                        and
                        <hotlnk document="s040402_X0404013.xml" xrefid="f0404068">(Figure 68)</hotlnk>
                        <xref refid="f0404068"/>
                        and caliper mounting bolts
                        <hotlnk document="s040402_X0404013.xml" xrefid="f0404071">(Figure 71)</hotlnk>
                        <xref refid="f0404071"/>.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f0404001" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg04/G0404001.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                         scalefitheight="472px"/>
